The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ruchi Soya gets AGM date relief

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Sept. 5: The Madhya Pradesh-based Ruchi Soya Industries has got the permission of the registrar of companies to extend the date of its annual general meeting by three months. The company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange that two of the three schemes of arrangement and amalgamation towards consolidation of 10 companies of the group have been completed. It is yet to get approval for the third scheme of amalgamation from the high courts of Mumbai and New Delhi.

 The company will now hold its annual general meeting on or before December 29.

 The Ruchi group had proposed the consolidation of similar businesses across the group. The company has obtained permission for the first two schemes from the Mumbai high court. 




